    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_40.Puzzles.and.Problems.in.Probability.and.Mathematical.Statistics,.Schwarz,.Springer,.2008_page_064_3",
    "text": "a. Clearly, if he orders no milk at all, there will be no gain and no loss, G(0) = 0. For very small c, the man will almost certainly sell his entire lot c, thereby gaining c(s-b). Thus, for small c, the net gain G will increase linearly with slope s - b and thus be positive. For very large c, almost surely not all stocked milk will be sold; in this situation, each additional unit stocked will impose an additional loss of b. Thus, for c large, G will decrease linearly with slope -b. Therefore, G must have at least one positive maximum for c > 0.",
