  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_40.Puzzles.and.Problems.in.Probability.and.Mathematical.Statistics,.Schwarz,.Springer,.2008_page_064_20",
    "text": "b. If he orders c units and sells only some of them, 0 ≤ d ≤ c, then the conditional expected net gain G(c|D = d) will be equal to d(s - b) - (c - d)b because his gain from the d units sold is d(s-b), and the cost of the remaining c - d nonsold units is (c - d)b. On the other hand, if d ≥ c he will sell all c units, yielding G(c|D = d) = c(s - b).",
